MATPOWER makeYbus
-----------------

Earlier internal copies of this project included a local `makeY.m` based on
MATPOWER's `makeYbus.m`. That local copy has been removed. Current HEBCPF
code calls MATPOWER's installed `makeYbus` directly instead of redistributing
the function.

MEX Binaries
------------

The MEX releases include precompiled Windows 64-bit MATLAB `.mexw64` files for
selected hot-path routines. They are provided for convenience. Users on other
platforms should rebuild them with `build_mex` and MATLAB Coder, or use one of
the pure MATLAB releases.

SuiteSparse/KLU and klurf
-------------------------

Package 2026.07.14 includes an optional KLU-accelerated bordered Newton solve.
The MEX release folders include `klurf.mexw64`. MATLAB v2/v3 can use a compatible
`klurf` binary; MATLAB v4 deliberately uses MATLAB built-ins only. The top-level `klurf/` folder
contains the HEBCPF-specific MEX wrapper source (`klurf_mex.c`), build helper
(`klurf_make.m`), and build notes.

`klurf` links against SuiteSparse/KLU and related SuiteSparse components,
including AMD, COLAMD, BTF, and SuiteSparse_config. SuiteSparse is authored
and maintained by Timothy A. Davis and contributors:

  https://github.com/DrTimothyAldenDavis/SuiteSparse

KLU and related SuiteSparse components are distributed under their own license
terms, including GNU LGPL-2.1-or-later terms for KLU. Users who rebuild,
modify, or redistribute the KLU-linked MEX must review the authoritative
SuiteSparse license texts and meet the applicable redistribution requirements.

